  <h2 id="prevention">Pest Prevention</h2>
  <p>
    <br>
    <li>Make sure your plants are planted or placed in locations suitable for them. This includes proper sunlight, soil, drainage, and temperature. Never plant something which is invasive to the local area!</li>
    <li>Plan your plants! Pest resistant plants and companion planting can help to prevent future pest issues.</li>
    <li>Keep your plants healthy. Healthy plants are less vulnerable to pests (and disease). </li>
    <li>Keep a lookout. By regularly checking your plants for signs of pests (or diseases) you are able to correct issues before they get out of hand. </li>
    <li>Prune selectively. Over-pruning can cause stress to the plant and leave it weak and vulnerable.</li>
    <li>Encourage beneficial insects. Learn to recognize the insects that help manage pests and let them keep up the good work. </li>
  </p>
 
